  "texts": [
    "Intent-driven management involves guiding and automating network operations by defining high-level business goals or desired outcomes.",
    "Unlike traditional network management, intent-driven management emphasizes \"what to do\" rather than \"how to do it.\"",
    "Administrators need only to define the desired effect to be achieved by the network, and the intelligent system automatically handles the specific implementation.",
    "As the enabling technology of NDTs, intentdriven management plays a crucial role in autonomous intent parsing, policy generation, closed-loop operation, iterative optimization, and policy validation (Fig. 25).",
    "Autonomous intent parsing."
